nmap - is a tool used to discover, scan, and analyze networks and systems.
 
MAIN ONES TO USE
-v verbose
-sS – TCP SYN scan (stealth scan, most popular)
-sA – ACK scan (firewall detection)
-T0 → -T5 – Timing templates (slow → insane fast)
-p <ports> – Specify ports
-f – Fragment packets
-sC – Run default scripts

-sI <zombie_host>
-D <decoy1,decoy2,...>

   Basic Scan Types
    -sS – TCP SYN scan (stealth scan, most popular)
    -sT – TCP connect scan (full connection) SLOW
    -sU – UDP scan
    -sA – ACK scan (firewall detection)
    -sW – Window scan
    -sM – Maimon scan
    -sN – Null scan
    -sF – FIN scan
    -sX – Xmas scan
    
 Target and Port Selection - 65535 possible ports
    -p <ports> – Specify ports 
        -p 80,443
        -p 80-443
        -p- for all
    --top-ports <n> – Scan most common ports
    -iL <file> – Input list of targets
    --exclude <host> – Exclude target(s)
    --open – Show only open ports

 Speed & Timing
    -T0 → -T5 – Timing templates (slow → insane fast)
    -T4 is the usual default for speed
    --min-rate <num> – Minimum packets/sec
    --max-rate <num> – Max packets/sec

Script Engine (NSE)
    -sC – Run default scripts
    --script <name> – Run specific scripts
    --script=vuln – Vulnerability scripts
    --script=auth – Authentication scripts
    --script=discovery – Network discovery

 -Pn – Skip host discovery (treat as alive)
    -f – Fragment packets
    --spoof-mac <mac> – Spoof MAC address
    --randomize-hosts – Randomize scan order
    --source-port <port> – Set source port


